The paper deals with computational problems related to decision-making, optimization, and query answering, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methods proposed in the paper involve clustering and iterative computation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of distance functions and the modification of search algorithms, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and data structures (cs.DS), respectively. Finally, the paper applies the proposed methods to phylogeny reconstruction and planning problems, which are topics in databases (cs.DB).
